        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 24 at 4:26PM EDT until August 24 at 5:00PM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 426 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Bridgeport, or
12 miles northwest of Oneida, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Rome, Oneida, Lee, Verona, Vienna, Sylvan Beach, Blossvale, New
London, Verona Beach, and Bridgeport.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Heavy rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to flash
flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
